Valve has banned over 40,000 Steam accounts following its annual Steam Summer Sale. The day after the sale concluded, a record 40,445 Steam accounts received a VAC (Valve anti-cheat) ban for cheating, according to data from SteamDB. The VAC ban wave was the biggest in Steamâ€™s history, eclipsing the previous record of 15,227 VAC bans. An additional 5,000 users received game bans on 6 July, which ban an account from playing a certain game online.